The normal distribution and the log-normal distribution are two different types of probability distributions that have distinct characteristics and applications. While they are related in some ways, they have key differences that set them apart.

1. Basic Definitions
Normal Distribution: Also known as the Gaussian distribution, this is a symmetric, bell-shaped distribution that describes many naturally occurring phenomena, such as heights, IQ scores, and measurement errors. It is defined for all real numbers and characterized by two parameters: the mean (μ) and the standard deviation (σ).

